definition.value: An amino disaccharide consisting of a 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-beta-D-galactopyranose residue and a 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-D-galactopyranose residue joined in sequence by a (1->6) glycosidic bond.
A glycosylgalactose consisting of alpha-L-fucopyranose and alpha-D-galactopyranose residues joined in sequence by a (1->2) glycosidic bond.
An amino disaccharide consisting of 2-amino-2-deoxy-alpha-D-glucopyranose and 2-amino-2-deoxy-D-glucopyranose residues joined in sequence by a (1->6) glycosidic bond.
A 3-D-galactosyl glycerol in which the carbon bearing the anomeric hydrogen has beta configuration.
